@node LEGAL_STUFF
@title "Legal Stuff"

1) Legal Stuff

1.1) Disclaimer

    HK-DLGTools are provided "AS IS", WITHOUT ANY WARRANTY to its
    quality, performance or fitness for a particular purpose.  In
    no event shall the author be liable or responsible to the user
    or any other person, for any kind of damage caused by the use
    of this software.

1.2) Conditions of Use and Distribution

    HK-DLGTools are MessageWare, if you like and use them send me a
    message (Internet or Fido).  Feel free to include complaints or
    suggestions.

    HK-DLGTools may be freely distributed provided:

       1. The files are ALL left intact and unmodified.

       2. No charge is made for HK-DLGTools (other than a reasonable copy 
          charge).

       3. HK-DLGTools is not packaged as a part of a commercial product 
          without prior written consent.

       4. HK-DLGTools may not be uploaded to any electronic service that
          claims a copyright to it's files and programs.

1.3) System Requirements and Limitations

    HK-DLGTools requires AmigaDOS V2.04 or higher and 50K memory.

@endnode


@node SYSTEM_DESC
@title "System Description"

2) System Description

HK-DLGTools is a set of simple utilities for the Dialog BBS system.
So far this set is comprised of three programs:

 @{" CommentDLGDir 37.2 " LINK COMMENTDLGDIR} - Copies the file or message area description
                        from Areas.bbs to the filenote for each 
                        numbered directory.

 @{" DLGFList 37.4 " LINK DLGFLIST}      - Creates a list of files available in all or 
                        some of your file areas. 

 @{" CreateFD 37.4 " LINK CREATEFD}      - Creates *.fd for files that already exist in 
                        a File storage area, like cd's for example. 

@endnode

@node INSTALLATION
@title "Installing HK-DLGTools"

3) Installation

To install HK-DLGTools, simply copy the HK-DLGTools programs to a
convenient place in your system and HK-DLGTools.guide and
HK-DLGTools.guide.info where ever you keep your docs.

@endnode

@node COMMENTDLGDIR
@title "CommentDLGDir CLI Usage"

4) CommentDLGDir CLI Usage.

This command is handy if you can't remember what file area number
contains what files.  When you LIST File:  or MSG:  the comment
contains the same string displayed in the area list when you are on
line.

    Command Template: ROOT/M,CLEAR/S

        ROOT  - One or more root directories to comment.
                Default is File: and MSG:.

        CLEAR - Remove all filenote instead of adding them.

4.1 @{" Sample Directory listing " LINK SAMPLEDIR}

@endnode

