@node DLGFLIST
@title "DLGFList CLI Usage"

5) DLGFList CLI Usage.

Yet another file list generator.  What can I say...  I didn't have one
and could not find one in the short search I made, so I killed a
couple of hours and threw this together.

    Command Template: ROOT,LIST/K,S=SHORT/S,W=WIDTH/N,START/N,END/N

        ROOT  - Root directory to scan.  Default is File:

        LIST  - Name of the output file.

        SHORT - Create short form output.  Only the first non-blank
                line from the descrition is inserted.

        WIDTH - Line width.  Default is 80 characters.

        START - First area number to catalogue.

        END   - Last area number to catalogue.


5.1 @{" Sample Standard Output " LINK STDOUTPUT}

5.2 @{" Sample Short Output " LINK SHRTOUTPUT}


Note: The number in parentases () after the file number is the area
      number.

@endnode

