@node CREATEFD
@title "CreateFD CLI Usage"

6) CreateFD CLI Usage.

This program creates the .fd for files that are already in place.  It
checks the Area.bbs file for the optional alternate storage path and
uses it or the area number to locate the file in order to get the file
size.  The file descrition can be entered on the command line or
copied from a file.

    Command Template: FILE/A,AREA/A,UPLOADER/A,DESC=DESCRIPTION/K,FROMFILE/S

        FILE        - Base name of file (ie no path).  This file must exist
                      in either the file area or the alternate storage area.

        AREA        - Area number for file.

        UPLOADER    - Person or thing to give credit to.

        DESCRIPTION - Descrition string or filename.

        FROMFILE    - Tells the program that DESCRIPTION is a file name.


@endnode

